headline: Is Qualcomm’s Embrace of Arm v9 a Sign of Enduring Strength for ARM?
summary: In recent days, Qualcomm announced it will use Arm Holdings' v9 architecture in its latest chips for PCs and smartphones, shortly after a U.S. court ruled in Qualcomm's favor in an ongoing licensing dispute with Arm. Arm Holdings also introduced its advanced Lumex compute subsystem platform, aimed at powering AI experiences and offering partners increased customization for next-generation devices. This series of events highlights Arm's sustained influence in shaping next-generation...
